review_blob: Brewed with the Westmalle yeast strain.  A wonderful blend of hops and yeast.  Not my favorite Belgian style but, its good.
beer_name: Lagunitas A Little Sumpin Wild Ale

review_blob: Floral, lemon, citrus, herbs. Loaded with hops. Not overly bitter.  Balanced very well. This is one of my go to double ipas.
Coffee, caramel, chocolate notes. Dark as used motor oil. Tan head that dissolves into a small rim around the top. Good lacing. Not too boozy.
Caramel, ginger, licorice, raisin flavors.  Alcohol is strong in this one. Decent offering from the local craft brewery.
beer_name: Schlafly Reserve Barleywine Style Ale Aged On Oak

review_blob: This is my favorite beer of all time. The best I have ever had. Lots of plum, cherry,  and yeast flavors. Alcohol is there but, not overpowering.
